[SPEAKER_04]: Paul has previously been interviewed by the charter committee.

282
00:26:42,534 --> 00:26:50,801
[SPEAKER_04]: So this was just specifically, I had just asked him a couple of quick questions and said, you know, short answers was fine.

283
00:26:51,541 --> 00:26:58,467
[SPEAKER_04]: So in response to what is your ideal term for school committee term?

284
00:26:59,261 --> 00:27:05,887
[SPEAKER_04]: two, three, if we could do it, which is questionable, or four years, he said four or three.

285
00:27:07,728 --> 00:27:11,352
[SPEAKER_04]: Would a four-year term have lessened your willingness to run initially?

286
00:27:12,212 --> 00:27:13,173
[SPEAKER_04]: Is it too daunting?

287
00:27:13,353 --> 00:27:17,217
[SPEAKER_04]: His answer to that was no, that it would be great.

288
00:27:19,158 --> 00:27:23,983
[SPEAKER_04]: When asked wards or at large for the school committee, Paul said all at large.

289
00:27:25,150 --> 00:27:28,892
