290
00:27:30,132 --> 00:27:32,794
[SPEAKER_04]: He says not chair and not on the committee at all.

291
00:27:34,935 --> 00:27:36,175
[SPEAKER_04]: Do you favor term limits?

292
00:27:36,615 --> 00:27:40,917
[SPEAKER_04]: He says, no, I've seen this in action in Newton and don't think it is a good idea.

293
00:27:41,578 --> 00:27:43,739
[SPEAKER_04]: As you know, the learning curve is very steep.

294
00:27:44,159 --> 00:27:47,880
[SPEAKER_04]: The knowledge required for this job could easily take a decade to acquire.

295
00:27:48,461 --> 00:27:53,143
[SPEAKER_04]: Let the voters decide when someone is done serving the community or the member is done.

296
00:27:55,225 --> 00:28:01,550
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay, 1, interesting thing that he said there in regards to the.

297
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:06,133
[SPEAKER_01]: I think it was the 4 year and the 3 year is just not all of us at once.

298
00:28:06,614 --> 00:28:08,735
[SPEAKER_01]: So, was he referring there to staggered terms?

299
00:28:09,876 --> 00:28:10,917
[SPEAKER_04]: He would be returning.

